<TEXT>
a warehouse custodian says a few days before he 
found the body of polar explorer richard e byrds son he ran him 
off the property because he thought he was a drifter 
police said richard e byrd jrs body was found last week in 
the debrisstrewn warehouse the body was clad in workmans clothes 
and one shoe although byrd had left boston by train wearing a tan 
shirt and brown pants for a national geographic society ceremony in 
washington dc honoring his father 
burt w gayleard the onsite manager for time realty which 
owns the warehouse said he spotted byrd and an unidentified man 
sept 27 
the first time i came across him he said somebody take me 
to baltimore i want to go to baltimore gayleard recalled he 
was trying to sleep when i found him he didnt have any teeth and 
he spoke like a vagrant but he pronounced baltimore properly 
not like someone who lived here 
byrd 68 left boston on sept 13 to attend the ceremony 
honoring his fatherhe never arrived and his whereabouts remained a 
mystery for three weeks 
