trying to come to grips with it 
byrd said his father had suffered from some memory loss but 
hadnt wandered before 
police identified byrd through a boston transit authority 
identification card pinned to his undershorts 
byrds family has asked arlington national cemetery officials 
outside washington for permission to bury him there byrds sister 
katharine breyer said sunday 
baltimore police spokesman dennis hill said sunday that 
investigators were waiting for results from toxicology tests that 
might shed light on the cause of death 
although byrd appeared to be suffering from malnutrition and 
dehydration a cause of death remained undetermined 
