country since this administration took office the price of houses 
has raced ahead of peoples wages and has made it impossible for 
many people to buy the homes they grew up in 
george bush has no housing program he continued he has 
no solutions he has no new ideas 
dukakis blamed reagan administration cuts in housing programs 
for the escalation of homelessness in the past eight years and said 
much of the problem was rooted in the lack of affordable housing 
for young families 
the dukakis plan called home start would allow firsttime 
homebuyers to use their individual retirement account or other 
taxdeferred pension savings for a down payment on a home dukakis 
said the plan was a natural extension of the goal behind such 
accounts 
under current law young families can speculate on stocks or 
gold or soybean futures with these funds dukakis said home 
start will let them make the best investment they can in a home 
for their families 
dukakis in the speech said the program also would include 
provisions to lower down payments and closing costs and to raise 
borrowing limits on federally guaranteed mortgages he did not cite 
a cost estimate and campaign aides were not immediately available 
to discuss the plan 
dukakis said the program would complement his proposal for a 
national partnership for affordable housing which is modeled after 
a massachusetts program that uses some state money and agreements 
with private developers to build moderately priced housing for 
firsttime buyers 
george bush and his friends are satisfied they say all is 
well dukakis said dan quayle is the only cloud on their 
