over hawaii in 1982 
however defense lawyers appealed to the areos pagos greeces 
supreme court to revoke the decision to extradite 39yearold 
mohammed rashid the countrys highest judicial body will hear the 
case within a month 
there is a majority decision by the council for extradition 
its decision is based on a portion of the us request appeals 
court judge stavros gardikiotis said under greek law the appeals 
council examines cases that involve crimes committed outside greece 
gardikiotis said there was enough evidence presented by the 
united states to back up its charges that rashid planted a bomb 
aboard the jetliner a japanese teenager was killed and 15 people 
injured in the explosion 
the council rejected as insufficient other us claims 
linking rashid to the attempted 1982 bombing of another pan am 
jetliner in rio de janeiro brazil no details of the alleged 
bombing attempt were released in court 
the council had twice postponed hearing the extradition request 
for rashid a member of the palestine liberation organization and 
delayed issuing its decision for one week 
this decision is a blow to the plo rashid told the 
