this fastgrowing city next door to denver 
has set up a volunteer network of translators to help officials 
communicate with the asian hispanic and other immigrants arriving 
here 
estimates are that 8000 residents or 3 percent of auroras 
population dont speak english causing problems for police at 
accident and crime scenes they include speakers of pushto dari 
chippewa spanish czech farsi french greek hebrew hungarian 
urdu polish russian tagalog ukranian and sign language 
aurora has drafted an emergency handbook for police and fire 
