commander gen michel aoun a maronite naming him caretaker prime 
minister of a sixman military cabinet 
all three moslem officers named to the aoun cabinet refused to 
serve and moslem leaders declared allegiance to the incumbent 
government of acting prime minister salim hoss a syrianbacked 
sunni moslem 
under an unwritten covenant dating from lebanons independence 
from france in 1943 maronites have held the posts of president 
army commander and central bank governor the premier traditionally 
was a sunni and the parliament speaker a shiite 
christians were deemed to be the majority in 1943 moslems now 
comprise an estimated 55 percent of lebanons 4 million people 
however and demand an equal share of power 
