said a road to the summit had been closed for three days because 
of snowdrifts weather observer john howe said the summit had a low 
sunday of 14 degrees winds gusted to 70 mph sunday 
records compiled the us forest service and others indicate 
that 103 people have died on mount washington since 1849 the most 
recent apparently were two climbers killed in separate incidents in 
