<TEXT>
praise from critics and adoration from 
college students does not pay the rent for novelist fred exley 
he drives a 1974 oldsmobile he bought several months ago for 
600 lives in an apartment over a garage in upstate new york eats 
boiled potatoes and chicken noodle soup and has a will but no 
money 
but the 58yearold author whos first book a fans notes 
is considered an american classic is not looking for people to 
have some kind of corny romantic vision of him 
hes not looking for compassion because he already has composure 
i dont have any sympathy for myself in the sense that this is 
the life i chose for myself nobody chose it for me exley said 
in an interview at a friends house im not without my inner 
peace 
he says without a doubt in his gruff monotone voice that if 
he had wanted he could have been a handsomely paid vice president 
of public relations somewhere waiting to collect a big pension and 
driving a new expensive car instead he chose to roll the 
dice and write literature that has been described as sadly funny 
bonechillingly honest overpowering and passionate 
his new book last notes from home random house 1895 
is his third novel and the conclusion of an autobiographical 
triology that readers had to wait two decades for him to finish 
when exleys first novel was published in 1968 he received rave 
reviews won several awards and seemed on his way to becoming one 
of this countrys great authors seven years later his second 
book pages from a cold island came out to mixed reviews 
neither book sold very well and the excitement disappeared 
he didnt exactly reinvigorate the enthusiasm by taking 13 years 
to write last notes a period when he struggled with trying to 
figure out how to insert recurring themes into the new novel and to 
convince his publisher that he could complete the book 
now that its finished exley is hoping for a big comeback 
however he certainly isnt going out of his way to encourage the 
success of the book no tv talk shows no barrage of interviews in 
new york city 
in fact as his book starting showing up in book stores across 
the country in september exley was hiding out at the home of a 
former college roommate just outside syracuse ny from his 
apartment on wellesley island located about 30 miles from his 
hometown of watertown ny 
its not that exley is shy or reclusive or that he doesnt want 
to be bothered exley just isnt comfortable dealing with the 
scores of people he considers either phony or pretentious or both 
when college students stumble into the thousand islands club 
after driving all night from columbus ohio to see exley our 
god the author joins his friends in the finger pointing game of 
im not exley hes exley 
when he goes to his favorite bar in manhattan the famous 
literary haunt the lions head and he overhears two customers 
doing the celebritywatcher refrain thats fred exley where 
over there see he gets up and walks out 
last notes has brought exley even more fame 
with such colorful characters as james otwoomey an excessive 
and outrageous irishman who takes exley hostage in hawaii and 
robin glenn a stewardess and pathological liar who marries exley 
the novel is funny downright hilarious at times 
the author believes the book contains some of the funniest and 
most powerful writing hes ever done and that it probably has the 
most commercial appeal of his three novels 
as he talks his words are preceded and followed by various 
profanities used as tools of humor not anger his doleful and 
penetrating brown eyes usually look away 
his books tell the story of fred exley the alcoholic son of a 
watertown sports legend who travels from mental hospitals to 
taverns to living room couches to hawaii seeking fame and 
selfawareness 
while many of the events in the books from the electric shock 
therapy to two divorces to trying to shoot his teenage twin sister 
with an antique rifle are based on reality exley said hes never 
written a word about himself 
autobiography is impossible it never occurred to me to do 
that he said when i started out i said why do it that 
way i thought this would be different 
it doesnt matter how much of the book is true yes the author 
likes to drink vodka yes he likes attractive women yes he plays 
golf and yes hes a male chauvinist but the character is 
fictional 
from the letters i get i know that a lot of people dont 
understand that they dont realize i was employing a novelistic 
technique exley said they think im hunched over the 
typewriter with a water glass full of vodka sloshed when i write 
he said hes not guilty of drinking while writing ive never 
written a line even with a hangover 
because he shares the same name and similar life with his main 
character many people who read exley believe they know him like 
the nextdoor neighbor college students in particular they 
affectionately and fondly write to him telling him how insightful 
and perceptive he is then they leave large blocks of space for 
his reply 
what theyre asking you to do is write their term paper for 
them those go right in the trash basket exley said they 
think im so lyrical and i sit around and talk about james joyce 
and ernest hemingway when actually i go to the bar and talk 
about the same thing that the college girls father who sells 
refrigerators talks about 
exley warns readers to stay on their toes with the closing scene 
of last notes 
robin who has been cited for her endless delusions and lies 
seems to add a final fantasy to the heap by telling exley she can 
surf quite well exley of course believes it to be another wild 
tale 
but then she climbs on the surfboard in her grandmothers 
wedding gown and effortlessly puts on a surfing exhibition 
robin who lies all the time obviously doesnt maybe exley 
the author who writes about himself all the time doesnt either 
perhaps the insistence of equating the character with the author 
will subside anyway now that exley is working on his fourth book 
a spy thriller that will introduce a new main character dan 
gunther a st lawrence university professor and exgreen beret 
im sick and tired of that exley guy he said 
will this new book take 13 years to finish 
no way i aint gonna live 13 years 
