<TEXT>
in a scene from the futuristic movie robocop a shiny silver 
disc is inserted into a playback machine to produce a recorded 
audiovideo message on a wall of television monitors 
video from what looks like a compact disc 
yes and you dont have to wait until the year 2000 to have 
cdvideo in your home actually there were laser videodiscs before 
audio compact discs the videodisc format dates back to 1978 
this year laser video is trying to create a new image its 
being touted as cdvideo a format that offers the best of both 
worlds to audiovideophiles 
like its audio cd cousin the videodiscs offer true digital 
sound on many programs but instead of just music the library of 
videodiscs includes classic and current movies concerts 
educational material and operas 
cdvideo programming appears on discs of three different sizes 
5 8 and 12inch 
the 5inch gold cdvideo singles have a capacity of five 
minutes of digital audio with video plus 20 minutes of additional 
digital audio per side 
programming on the 8 and 12inch discs theyre silvercolored 
are primarily all videoaudio the 8inch discs can hold up to 20 
minutes of both video and audio material per side the 12inch 
discs boost the time to 60 minutes per side 
players currently in playbackonly format are manufactured by 
pioneer magnavox yamaha and sony 
players can be bought for under 500 but one with all the 
frills will list out at about 2000 some of the players use only 
the 8 and 12inch videodiscs but newer combination models 
play all consumer optical discs 
no matter which player is selected the audiovideo quality 
cannot be matched signaltonoise ratio on the audio portion of 
cdvideo players is rated 97 decibels or better the players offer 
420425 lines of horizontal resolution providing an exceptional 
picture 
since the discs are read by a lowpower laser beam there is 
no wear on them 
cdvideo singles list for about 10 with feature films ranging 
from 35 to 50 in many instances a movie on laser video will 
cost less than videotape 
cdvideo also offers jitterfree freeze frame and slow motion 
plus a variety of other programming capabilities pick out a 
favorite song from an entire concert on a 12inch disc and the 
player can search it out in a matter of seconds and play it 
consumers can also program a player to scan for a single frame of a 
movie and freeze it on the screen 
a search through a cdvideo brochure reveals art collections and 
an encyclopedia as well as games and programs from nasa national 
geographic and other special interest discs 
