paperworkers who walked out at international paper co mills here 
and in wisconsin and pennsylvania is ending after 16 months union 
officials said today 
the strike is over said john chouinard spokesman for local 
14 of the united paperworkers international union 
the decision was reached sunday after a series of meetings with 
union leaders from ip mills across the country said robert frase 
executive assistant to upiu president wayne glenn in nashville 
tenn 
the company was informed by telegram sunday he said 
international paper had continued to run its mills with 
